  "prompt": "How can I know who views my Instagram profile?",
  "response": "Instagram does not provide a way for users to see who has viewed their profile. This is a privacy feature that protects users' viewing habits. However, here are some alternatives you can consider:\n\n1. **Story Views**: You can see who views your Instagram Stories. If someone watches your Story, their username will appear in the list of viewers.\n\n2. **Post Engagement**: You can monitor likes, comments, and saves on your posts to see who is interacting with your content. \n\n3. **Third-Party Apps**: There are some third-party applications that claim to show you profile viewers, but most of these violate Instagram's terms of service and can compromise your account's security. It's advisable to avoid using them.\n\n4. **Business Account Insights**: If you have a business account, you can access insights that show engagement metrics, which can give you an idea of how many people are interacting with your content.\n\nInstagram prioritizes user privacy, so if you're looking for specific information about profile views, it won't be available.",
